Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2%unit(s)} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 2-3cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the chicken with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken, turn the heat down to medium and cook until golden brown, ~{7-8%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, cut the @medium tomato{1%unit(s)} into 2cm chunks.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @sugar{1%tsp}, @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} and @red wine vinegar{12%grams}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and mix well.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing and toss to coat. Set aside.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a board, cover with #foil{} and leave to rest while you cook the bacon.

Pop your pan back on medium heat (no need to clean). Lay in the @British Streaky Bacon{4%rasher(s)} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

While the bacon cooks, halve the @burger buns{2%unit(s)}. Pop them onto a baking tray and into oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, add the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} to the tomatoes and toss to coat in the dressing.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Spread the @onion marmalade{40%grams} over the bun bases and the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} on the lids. Top the bases with the chicken and crispy bacon rashers (2 per person), then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve on your plates with the wedges and salad alongside.

Enjoy!